cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.MM, cs.HC, cs.IR 

The paper discusses the design and prototype of an optical fingerprint reader that uses image processing techniques for spoof detection. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the security aspect of the fingerprint recognition system, which makes it relevant to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) category. The use of cameras and image processing techniques also makes it relevant to the cs.MM (Multimedia) category. The paper also discusses the usability aspect of the fingerprint recognition system, which makes it relevant to the cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) category. Finally, the paper discusses the interoperability of the RaspiReader with existing COTS optical readers, which makes it relevant to the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) category.
